OL,3,CBereaved mother vows to keep fighting
OL,4,Cfor maternity safety
OL,6,FRhiannon said: "I realised what I'd
OL,7,Fdone wasn't enough. So we carried on.
OL,8,FWhen you lose a baby you don't have
OL,9,Fmemories that can comfort with you.
OL,10,FYou don't have that natural grief
OL,11,Fprocess.
OL,13,F"You don't mourn. You are stuck
OL,14,Fforever wondering 'what the hell
OL,15,Fhappened'?", she added.
OL,17,FThe families decided to come together
OL,18,Fto call for answers and their
OL,19,Fexperiences have fed into a report led
OL,20,Fby senior midwife Donna Ockenden.
